notesStmt.note: Condition: Extensive worm damage, ff. 83-106, minor worm damage present throughout.

msContents.summary: A copy, probably made in the 17th century, of an alphabetical list of Spanish names, words, and phrases, with translations in Tzeltal.

msItem.title: Vocabulario de la lengua española y tzeldal

supportDesc.extent: 198 leaves : 202 x 145 mm. bound to 217 x 161 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 198 (no leaf 35, unnumbered leaf between 80 and 81); contemporary numbers, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Copied in two hands, ff. 1-120 and ff. 120-198.

origin.p: Probably copied in the 17th century, location unknown.

history.provenance: Bookplate inside front cover: Ex Collectione Americana, Domini Brasseur de Bourbourg.

A transcript of a portion of a 1922 letter from Adela C. Breton to G. B. Gordon attached to the pages before the manuscript suggests that this manuscript was not part of the Berendt collection but passed through the collections of the abbé Brasseur de Bourbourg, A. L. Pinart, and Eugène Boban before Daniel Garrison Brinton purchased it separately.
From the collection of Daniel Garrison Brinton (ex libris stamp on title page).
